  abstract  = {2nd ed. This book will introduce students to intelligent agents, explain what these agents are, how they are constructed and how they can be made to co-operate effectively with one another in large-scale systems. Intelligent Agents – Deductive Reasoning Agents – Practical Reasoning Agents – Reactive and Hybrid Agents – Understanding Each Other – Communicating – Working Together – Methodologies – Applications – Multiagent Interactions – Making Group Decisions – Forming Coalitions – Allocating Scarce Resources – Bargaining – Arguing – Logical Foundations.},
